                <fr:anchor>7718</fr:anchor>
                <fr:addr type="user">jms-00NO</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>jms-00NO.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Characterisation of well-foundness in terms of chains">Characterisation of <fr:link href="jms-00NL.xml" title="Well-founded relation" addr="jms-00NL" type="local">well-foundness</fr:link> in terms of chains</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Proposition</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:p>A relation <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\prec \colon  A\mathbin {\nrightarrow } A]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="jms-00NL.xml" title="Well-founded relation" addr="jms-00NL" type="local">well-founded</fr:link> if and only if there are no infinite descending <html:span style="white-space: nowrap" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\prec ]]></fr:tex>-chains</html:span> in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>, i.e. no infinite sequences <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a_0,a_1,\ldots ,a_i,\ldots ]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a_0\succ  a_1\succ \cdots  a_i\succ \cdots ]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
